fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.http

Interface IRequestHeaders

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<String>

    public interface IRequestHeaders
extends Iterable<String>
    Provides access to HTTP request headers. This does not include access to the method, URI, or protocol version.

    Instances of this interface can be used directly in for-each loops, to iterate over header names.

    Thread-safety: implementations of this interface are not required to be safe for concurrent access. Therefore, processing should generally not be shared between multiple threads.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IHttpServiceCall.getRequestHeaders()

      • getBasicAuthentication

        IBasicAuthn getBasicAuthentication()
        Gets authentication information submitted by the client using the basic HTTP authentication protocol, if provided.

        Character encoding is assumed to be ISO-8859-1 as per RFC-2617. However, different web browsers apply different (and incompatible) rules for encoding non-ASCII characters, which may cause unexpected results.

        Note: any information returned by this method should not be used beyond the duration of a transaction, and should not be stored in the JVM's memory heap, to avoid exposing passwords via memory-scanning security tools.

        Returns:
        the decoded authentication principal and credentials submitted by the client, or null if no information was provided in the request (or if it could not be decoded).
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IHttpServiceCall.sendBasicChallenge(CharSequence)

      • getBasicAuthentication

        IBasicAuthn getBasicAuthentication(Charset encoding)
        Gets authentication information submitted by the client using the basic HTTP authentication protocol and the specified character encoding, if provided.

        Note: any information returned by this method should not be used beyond the duration of a transaction, and should not be stored in the JVM's memory heap, to avoid exposing passwords via memory-scanning security tools.

        Parameters:
        encoding - the character encoding, defaulting to ISO-8859-1 if unspecified.
        Returns:
        the decoded authentication principal and credentials submitted by the client, or null if no information was provided in the request (or if it could not be decoded).
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        IHttpServiceCall.sendBasicChallenge(CharSequence)

        List<IMediaType> getAcceptableMediaTypes()
        Gets an ordered list of media types acceptable by the client.
        Returns:

      • getAcceptableCharsets

        List<Charset> getAcceptableCharsets()
        Gets an ordered list of character encodings acceptable by the client.

        This does not provide any reliable indication of the character encoding used to encode the request body (if there is one).

        Returns:
        a list (possibly empty, never null) containing the list of character encodings the client is prepared to accept (starting with the highest preference). For encodings with equal preference, the order is arbitrary.
        Since:
        1.0
